1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 39-10-43 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to railroad crossings.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 39-10-43 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 39-10-43. Certain vehicles must stop at all railroad grade crossings.
7 1. The driver of a bus carrying passengers, or of a schoolbus, or of a vehicle carrying
8 chlorine, empty or loaded cargo tank vehicles used to transport dangerous articles or
9 any liquid having a flashpoint below two hundred degrees Fahrenheit [93.33 degrees
10 Celsius], cargo tank vehicles transporting a commodity having a temperature above its
11 flashpoint at the time of loading, certain cargo tank vehicles transporting commodities
12 under special permits issued by the hazardous materials regulations board, and every
13 motor vehicle which must have the following placards: "explosives", "poison",
14 "flammable oxidizers", "compressed gas", "corrosives", "flammable gas", "radioactive",
15 or "dangerous", before crossing at grade any track of a railroad, shall stop the vehicle
16 within fifty feet [15.24 meters] but not less than fifteen feet [4.57 meters] from the
17 nearest rail of the railroad and while stopped shall listen and look in both directions
18 along the track for any approaching train or other on-track equipment, and for signals
19 indicating the approach of a train or other on-track equipment and may not proceed
20 until the driver can do so safely. After stopping as required and upon proceeding when
21 safe to do so, the driver of the vehicle shall cross only in such gear of the vehicle that
22 there will be no necessity for manually changing gears while traversing the crossing
23 and the driver may not shift gears manually while crossing the track.
