1 2. A stop is not required at a crossing if traffic is controlled by a police officer. For the
2 purposes of this section, a United States marshal is considered a police officer.
3 3. A stop is not required at a crossing that the director has designated as an
4 out-of-service or exempt crossing and which is clearly marked by signs bearing the
5 words "Tracks out of service" or "Exempt" in conspicuous places on each side of the
6 crossing.
7 4. The designation must be limited to use at a crossing where track has been abandoned
8 or its use discontinued.
9 5. The director shall notify the road authority and any railway company of a crossing
10 under the jurisdiction of that railway company which the director has designated as an
11 out-of-service crossing under this section and the road authority shall erect signs
12 bearing the words "Tracks out of service" or "Exempt" in conspicuous places on each
13 side of the crossing.
14 6.5. All signs must conform to the manual on uniform traffic-control devices as provided
15 under section 39-13-06.
